The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and Governor Rick Scott during a visit to Lynn Haven, Florida after Hurricane Michael hit the area. President Trump thanked the first responders, FEMA, and law enforcement for their work in responding to the storm. Governor Scott praised the coordination and assistance provided by FEMA and expressed gratitude for the President's support. President Trump acknowledged the extensive damage caused by the storm and praised the recovery efforts. He also mentioned that relief efforts are being prioritized and that assistance is being provided to both Florida and Georgia, which were also affected by the hurricane. The President and Governor Scott both commended the resilience and unity of the community in the face of the disaster. The remarks ended with President Trump interacting with volunteers who were assisting in the recovery efforts.